**********************************************************************
MAUI auplay demo code
**********************************************************************
What this demo does:
  - Plays audio files that are in the .wav or the Sun
	Microsystems .au formats.
  - There is an extensive set of command line options.  Type -? or -h
	on the command line to display the options.

*********************************************************************
System requirements:
  - A working MAUI environment is assumed.
  - The demo requires that a sound descriptor and a sound driver are
	in memory.
  - The demo requires that mfm is in memory.
  - .wav or .au sound files must be available as assets.

*********************************************************************
Directories: 
  - Source code 
       $MWOS/SRC/MAUI/DEMOS/SND
        
*********************************************************************
To make this demo:
  - From the source file directory type:
      % os9make
*********************************************************************
NOTE: The Sound Driver Interface only supports WAV type 0x39 files,
	  it does not support WAV type 0x11 files.





**********************************************************************
MAUI aurecord demo code
**********************************************************************
What this demo does:
  - Records audio files to the .wav or the Sun Microsystems .au
	formats.
  - There is an extensive set of command line options.  Type -? or -h
	on the command line to display the options.

*********************************************************************
System requirements:
  - A working MAUI environment is assumed.
  - The demo requires that a sound descriptor and a sound driver are
	in memory.
  - The demo requires that mfm is in memory.

*********************************************************************
Directories: 
  - Source code 
       $MWOS/SRC/MAUI/DEMOS 
        
*********************************************************************
To make this demo:
  - From the source file directory type:
      % os9make
*********************************************************************
NOTE: The Sound Driver Interface only supports WAV type 0x39 files,
	  it does not support WAV type 0x11 files.


